{"TopicId":138186,"ForumId":51,"TopicTitle":"A plane to land, explore and Escape from Eve","CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-26T17:17:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-26T17:17:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is my mission to Eve with a plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe goal was to design a plane able to:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Enter Eve Atmosphere and land\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Explorer Eve\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Leave Eve and join an orbiting shuttle to return to Kerbin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Torch nuclear turbojet engines from Atomic Age from Porkjet is able to run in oxygen less atmosphere without combustible, the downside being it is very heavy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo i designed an aircraft able to support a rocket that would be launched from the plane in flight to join a return shuttle in Eve orbit at 110kms\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6 big Torch nuclear turbojets motorized the aircraft up to 14kms altitude. Range is unlimited for exploration. Crew is only 1, but I will try a 2 crew cabin as the rocket is able to reach 110km when launched from 14kms.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe aircraft is very touchy to land on rough land and it is better to be helped by Pilot assistant. Speed brakes and repackable drag chutes will break it quickly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome ejectable experiment devices are included on the plane for science. Total weight on Eve is 210T. The rocket to orbit is a 59T rockets with a lot of stages\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the final take off to reach orbit, everything that is non necessary is ejected from the plane: Gears, Cooler system for Nuclear turbojets, Science devices, repackable drag chutes, speed brakes....This help the plane to reach 14kms before launching the rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDuring the launch the plane is destroyed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA 67T Ablators shield system protect the plane during Entry and Eve aerobraking provided the 8 ejectable vernors on the nose of the rocket keep the plane centered on retrograde. These vernors run on 2 ejectable tanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnder 15 kms 2 chutes combined with the vernors allow the plane to nose down to eject the ablator shield. Then vernors tanks, chutes and vernors are ejected while starting the nuclear turbojet.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is the launch with SpaceY engines and 5m tanks rocket launcher.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=982350screenshot377.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022982350screenshot377.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/982350screenshot377.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=881855screenshot381.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022881855screenshot381.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/881855screenshot381.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=863746screenshot385.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022863746screenshot385.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/863746screenshot385.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere we are with the breaking rocket, protected also by ablators shield for Eve aerobraking. The shield of the rocket are mounted on Hinges. They can open and close.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had to make a burn at 85 kms to reach an 10.000 kms Apoapsis, then I perform aerobraking up to a 102 km orbit. Initially, for Eve orbit interception\u00A0i was not able to set a Periapsis under 85kms, aerobraking was to hot and the whole thing would explode, so I had to burn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter the first burn I set the peri at 79.5 and aerobraked for around 20 tours, peri going down progressively to 75.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=987339screenshot397.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022987339screenshot397.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/987339screenshot397.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=698817screenshot399.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022698817screenshot399.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/698817screenshot399.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere we are at circular orbit 102 Kms. Note that a small shuttle on the top of the plane near the 2 chutes that will helped to eject the shied and nose down under 15kms\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=597482screenshot405.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022597482screenshot405.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/597482screenshot405.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShuttle ejection\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=748615screenshot406.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022748615screenshot406.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/748615screenshot406.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEntering after last burn\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=934753screenshot427.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022934753screenshot427.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/934753screenshot427.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBreaking rocket ejection\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=820714screenshot434.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022820714screenshot434.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/820714screenshot434.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=135998screenshot435.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022135998screenshot435.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/135998screenshot435.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExplosion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=134429screenshot437.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022134429screenshot437.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/134429screenshot437.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDescending and breaking on retrograde\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=644584screenshot439.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022644584screenshot439.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/644584screenshot439.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=203636screenshot440.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022203636screenshot440.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/203636screenshot440.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinal descent before opening chutes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=203636screenshot440.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022203636screenshot440.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/203636screenshot440.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChutes opened\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=221959screenshot455.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022221959screenshot455.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/221959screenshot455.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShield ejected\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=297862screenshot468.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022297862screenshot468.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/297862screenshot468.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNuclear engines started and vernors tanks and chutes ejected\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=559058screenshot469.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022559058screenshot469.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/559058screenshot469.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn final for landing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=301112screenshot470.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022301112screenshot470.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/301112screenshot470.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShort final 80m/s on Pilot assistant, plane being touchy and fragile for landing. \u00A0In flight it can bear many g up to the red gauge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=569462screenshot473.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022569462screenshot473.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/569462screenshot473.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn ground breaking\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=244914screenshot476.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022244914screenshot476.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/244914screenshot476.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKneeling the plane to allow Jeb out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=648525screenshot477.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022648525screenshot477.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/648525screenshot477.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCollecting experiment\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=835491screenshot478.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022835491screenshot478.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/835491screenshot478.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRepacking chutes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=906942screenshot479.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022906942screenshot479.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/906942screenshot479.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack to cockpit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hostingpics.net/viewer.php?id=951545screenshot481.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022951545screenshot481.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://img11.hostingpics.net/pics/951545screenshot481.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNext time we take off for exploration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExploration flights here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/138661-exploring-eve-with-my-205t-atomic-plane/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-02T13:46:31Z\u0022 title=\u002205/02/2016 01:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by gilflo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geschosskopf","CreatedById":69507,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-27T04:35:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGeez, what a monster. \u00A0Good luck with getting back up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-27T08:05:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can see here an escape to a 110km orbit with the previous remote version of Eve Escaper (nearly similar- on this one I add, science stuff, \u00A0repackable chutes, speed brakes and cooling system to fly unlimited time, all ejectable to climb to 14kms)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook after mn 3.30\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/3u5Fj7DIOY0?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-01T16:44:08Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2016 04:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 1, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by gilflo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gilflo","CreatedById":62881,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T13:46:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExploration flights here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/138661-exploring-eve-with-my-205t-atomic-plane/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}